    "sections": {
        "description": "<p><strong>This plugin is not required anymore. From Post Pay Counter v2.780 (2023-06-07), Slimstat and other visits trackers are supported natively without need of extra addons.</strong></p>\n<p>This little addon allows integration of WP-Slimstat visits data with Post Pay Counter. This way, you will be able to use Post Pay Counter to pay your writers per visit using the tracking functions of WP-Slimstat.</p>\n<p>Requires both <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/post-pay-counter/\" rel=\"ugc\">Post Pay Counter</a> and <a href=\"https://it.wordpress.org/plugins/wp-slimstat/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">WP-Slimstat</a> (both free).</p>\n",
        "installation": "<p>See <a href=\"http://postpaycounter.com/pay-writers-per-visit-wordpress/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">this page</a>, section WP-Slimstat.</p>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.1 (2017/01/22)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: visits not showing in <a href=\"https://postpaycounter.com/ppcp-display-stats-in-public-pages-with-post-pay-counter-pro-shortcode/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">shortcode stats</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0 (2016/06/06)</h4>\n<p>Initial release</p>\n"
